Perfect — next is Batch 4: 130-packages.

For this section, I would keep the package selections clean and not mix in site-specific things like Chrome, VS Code, NVIDIA scripts, domain join, proxy setup, or internal repo cleanup. Those belong in 140-post, 200-extras, Ansible, or a later handoff hook.

Kickstart package selections go inside %packages and must close with %end; packages can be selected by environment, group, module, or package name, and Red Hat points users to the ISO/repo comps metadata for the exact environment/group names available for that release.  ￼

